messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Ma'am, emergency at 5801 Eagle Drive.
I'm trying to get an ambulance to you. Hang on a minute. What's going on, ma'am?
I don't have a gun.
What's the address again?
6901 Call Street, Linda Vista, and Willowbrook.
Attention, 901 in medical emergency. It may be a possible stabbing. 5801 Eagle Drive, box C-38.
Can't me a car plant?
Oh, my God. Oh, my God. Oh, my God.
5801 Eagle Drive. What's therapy on the phone?
Hold on. You said your child has been stabbed?
Oh, my God, Rick. Can you hear?
Ma'am, I need you to calm down and talk to me, okay? Please.
5801 Eagle. 303 cold.
Ma'am, listen to me.
Yes, yes.
I need you to talk to me. I can't understand you. You're going to have to slow down, calm down, and talk to me.
They're dying. What is going on?
Somebody screamed. It was freaking me out. My little boys were sleeping. Somebody came in.
Stabbed me and my baby. I woke up and was fighting.
He ran out. My babies are dying. They're dead. Oh, my God!
Ma'am, stay on the phone, please.
Oh, my God. Oh, my God. Oh, my God.
Ma'am, who's there with you? Is there anybody in the house besides you and your children?
My husband. He just ran downstairs. He's helping me but he's done.
Okay. How many little boys? Is it two boys?
I love them. They're too!
Okay, listen to me, calm down.
5801 Eagle Drive. When are they going to be here?
Ma'am, they're on their way.
Ma'am, how old are your boys?
What?
How old are your boys?
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.
Did you name Dahlie?
Yes.
Your husband's name Dan?
Yes, please.
Holy God, they're taken forever.
Did nobody in your head?
There was. You don't know who did this? They were on the ground, I was fighting.
My baby, oh, my God. They left the knife. There's a knife.
Don't touch anything.
Oh, he caught him. Who's out there? Is anybody out there?
Okay, ma'am, listen. There's a police officer at your front door. Is your front door unlocked?
Yes, ma'am.
Hurry, please.
Okay, you need to let the officers in the front door, okay?
What?
You need to let the police officers in the front door.
I've already picked up the knife.
It's all right. Let the officers in.
What if we got in the press, baby?
Ma'am, hang on a second.
Nobody walked in here and did it, then. There's nothing cut.
Ma'am, is the police officer there?
Yes.
Okay, go talk to him, okay?
Okay.
